## if else

if (boolean expression)
{

}
else
{

}

### switch statement

permits enumeration of discrete cases, it's important to 'break' or else you fall through the cases

int x = getint();
switch(x)
{
    case 1:
        printf
        break;
    case 2:
        printf
        break;
    case 3:
        printf
        break;
}

###### ternary operator

int x = (expr) ? true : false;